&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse Band 5 Ward C5B - Permanent Contract&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary £24,907 - £30,615&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time and part time hours available (12 hour shifts)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Following a redesign of respiratory medicine we have an exciting opportunity for the right individual to join our team leading on the care and management of patients with respiratory conditions, C5B is a 24 bedded unit with a designated Lead nurse. We are looking for registered nurses to come and join our team, where you will be supported with a named mentor, the Lead nurses and the consultants. We can tailor your induction programme and ongoing level of support to your individual developmental needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a trust we offer exciting opportunities to further develop your skills in mentorship, in respiratory care, in non-invasive ventilation and in end of life care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are committed, compassionate and have an interest in developing and ensuring the best possible patient experience, then C5B needs you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will expect you to work flexibly and where possible we will support flexible working. Now is the right time we have a strengthened leadership team and together we can make a difference to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Elaine Foster Lead nurse C5B.&lt;/p&gt;
